 89  /-
 90  The coinductive predicate `pred`:
 91  
 92    coinductive {u} pred (A) : a → Prop
 93    | r : ∀A b, pred A p
 94  
 95  where
 96    `u` is a list of universe parameters
 97    `A` is a list of global parameters
 98    `pred` is a list predicates to be defined
 99    `a` are the indices for each `pred`
100    `r` is a list of introduction rules for each `pred`
101    `b` is a list of parameters for each rule in `r` and `pred`
102    `p` is are the instances of `a` using `A` and `b`
103  
104  `pred` is compiled to the following defintions:
105  
106    inductive {u} pred.functional (A) ([pred'] : a → Prop) : a → Prop
107    | r : ∀a [f], b[pred/pred'] → pred.functional a [f] p
108  
109    lemma {u} pred.functional.mono (A) ([pred₁] [pred₂] : a → Prop) [(h : ∀b, pred₁ b → pred₂ b)] :
110      ∀p, pred.functional A pred₁ p → pred.functional A pred₂ p
111  
112    def {u} pred_i (A) (a) : Prop :=
113    ∃[pred'], (Λi, ∀a, pred_i a → pred_i.functional A [pred] a) ∧ pred'_i a
114  
115    lemma {u} pred_i.corec_functional (A) [Λi, C_i : a_i → Prop] [Λi, h : ∀a, C_i a → pred_i.functional A C_i a] :
116      ∀a, C_i a → pred_i A a
117  
118    lemma {u} pred_i.destruct (A) (a) : pred A a → pred.functional A [pred A] a
119  
120    lemma {u} pred_i.construct (A) : ∀a, pred_i.functional A [pred A] a → pred_i A a
121  
122    lemma {u} pred_i.cases_on (A) (C : a → Prop) {a} (h : pred_i a) [Λi, ∀a, b → C p] → C a
123  
124    lemma {u} pred_i.corec_on (A) [(C : a → Prop)] (a) (h : C_i a)
125      [Λi, h_i : ∀a, C_i a → [V j ∃b, a = p]] : pred_i A a
126  
127    lemma {u} pred.r (A) (b) : pred_i A p
128  -/

216  /- compact_relation bs as_ps: Product a relation of the form:
217    R := λ as, ∃ bs, Λ_i a_i = p_i[bs]
218  This relation is user visible, so we compact it by removing each `b_j` where a `p_i = b_j`, and
219  hence `a_i = b_j`. We need to take care when there are `p_i` and `p_j` with `p_i = p_j = b_k`. -/
220  private meta def compact_relation :
221    list expr → list (expr × expr) → list expr × list (expr × expr)
id     └──┘ └──┘ ┴ └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘    └──┘ └──┘ ┴ └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘
src    └──┘ └──┘   └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘    └──┘ └──┘ ┴ └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘
typ    └──┘ └──┘ ┴ └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘    └──┘ └──┘ ┴ └──┘  └──┘ ┴ └──┘
doc         └──┘         └──┘   └──┘         └──┘         └──┘   └──┘
222  | [] ps      := ([], ps)
id     └┘ └┘         ┴└┘
src    └┘            ┴└┘
typ    └┘ └┘         ┴└┘
223  | (list.cons b bs) ps :=
id      └───────┘ ┴ └┘  └┘
src     └───────┘
typ     └───────┘ ┴ └┘  └┘
224    match ps.span (λap:expr × expr, ¬ ap.2 =ₐ b) with
id             └───┘      └──┘ ┴ └──┘  ┴ └┘┴  └┘
src            └───┘      └──┘ ┴ └──┘  ┴   ┴  └┘
typ            └───┘      └──┘ ┴ └──┘  ┴ └┘┴  └┘
doc                       └──┘   └──┘         └┘
225      | (_, [])           := let (bs, ps) := compact_relation bs ps in (b::bs, ps)
id         ┴   └┘               └─┘ ┴└┘  └┘     └──────────────┘          ┴ └┘
src        ┴   └┘                   ┴                                     ┴ └┘
typ        ┴   └┘               └─┘ ┴└┘  └┘     └──────────────┘          ┴ └┘
226      | (ps₁, list.cons (a, _) ps₂) := let i := a.instantiate_local b.local_uniq_name in
id         ┴└─┘  └───────┘ ┴┴     └─┘         ┴     └────────────────┘  └──────────────┘
src        ┴     └───────┘ ┴                        └────────────────┘  └──────────────┘
typ        ┴└─┘  └───────┘ ┴┴     └─┘         ┴     └────────────────┘  └──────────────┘
227        compact_relation (bs.map i) ((ps₁ ++ ps₂).map (λ⟨a, p⟩, (a, i p)))
id         └──────────────┘    └──┘ ┴        └┘     └─┘    ┴┴  ┴   ┴   ┴
src                            └──┘          └┘     └─┘            ┴
typ        └──────────────┘    └──┘ ┴        └┘     └─┘    ┴┴  ┴   ┴   ┴
228    end
